+# VNC Console and Screenshot Stability Tests
+
+## Overview
+
+This test module implements the test plan for **CNV-61271: VNC Console Disconnect Due to Thumbnail/Full Screen Competition**.
+
+## Background
+
+### Problem
+Previously, when users viewed a VM overview page (showing a thumbnail screenshot) while also having a full-screen VNC console open in another tab, the VNC connection would constantly disconnect. This was caused by both the thumbnail and full-screen VNC competing for the same VNC connection.
+
+### Solution
+The fix (PR [kubevirt/kubevirt#15238](https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/pull/15238)) changes the screenshot functionality to use libvirt's `virDomainScreenshot` API instead of VNC, eliminating the connection competition.
+
+## Test Coverage
+
+### Tier 1 Tests (Functional)
+
+#### TestVNCScreenshotStability
+
+1. **test_vnc_stability_with_concurrent_screenshot** (P0)
+   - Verifies VNC connection remains stable when screenshots are taken
+   - Polarion: CNV-61271
+   - Simulates the original bug scenario
+
+2. **test_screenshot_without_vnc_connection** (P0)
+   - Verifies screenshot API works without establishing VNC connection
+   - Polarion: CNV-61271
+   - Confirms screenshots use libvirt API, not VNC
+
+3. **test_screenshot_quality_verification** (P1)
+   - Verifies screenshot quality and format
+   - Polarion: CNV-61271
+   - Ensures screenshot functionality is usable
+
+4. **test_thumbnail_updates_without_vnc_impact** (P0)
+   - Verifies thumbnail refreshes don't impact active VNC
+   - Polarion: CNV-61271
+   - Core functionality test
+
+### Tier 2 Tests (E2E)
+
+#### TestVNCExtendedStability
+
+5. **test_extended_dual_usage** (P1)
+   - Tests extended dual-tab usage (5 minutes)
+   - Polarion: CNV-61271
+   - Verifies long-term stability
+
+#### TestMultiGuestOS
+
+6. **test_fedora_vm_screenshot_and_vnc** (P2)
+   - Tests Fedora guest OS compatibility
+   - Polarion: CNV-61271
+
+7. **test_rhel_vm_screenshot_and_vnc** (P2)
+   - Tests RHEL guest OS compatibility
+   - Polarion: CNV-61271
+
+8. **test_windows_vm_screenshot_and_vnc** (P2)
+   - Tests Windows guest OS compatibility
+   - Polarion: CNV-61271
+   - Marked with `@pytest.mark.high_resource_vm`
+
+## Test Structure
+
+```
+tests/virt/node/vnc_console/
+├── __init__.py
+├── README.md (this file)
+├── conftest.py (fixtures for test VMs)
+└── test_vnc_screenshot_stability.py (main test implementation)
+```
+
+## Fixtures
+
+All fixtures are defined in `conftest.py`:
+
+- `running_fedora_vm`: Fedora VM for testing
+- `running_rhel_vm`: RHEL VM for multi-OS testing
+- `running_windows_vm`: Windows VM for multi-OS testing
+
+## Running the Tests
+
+### Run all VNC console tests
+```bash
+pytest tests/virt/node/vnc_console/
+```
+
+### Run specific test classes
+```bash
+# Tier 1 tests only
+pytest tests/virt/node/vnc_console/ -m tier1
+
+# Tier 2 tests only
+pytest tests/virt/node/vnc_console/ -m tier2
+```
+
+### Run specific scenarios
+```bash
+# Scenario 1: VNC stability
+pytest tests/virt/node/vnc_console/test_vnc_screenshot_stability.py::TestVNCScreenshotStability::test_vnc_stability_with_concurrent_screenshot
+
+# Scenario 2: Screenshot without VNC
+pytest tests/virt/node/vnc_console/test_vnc_screenshot_stability.py::TestVNCScreenshotStability::test_screenshot_without_vnc_connection
+```
+
+### Run by Polarion ID
